The IPv6 ospfv3 {neighbor <neighbor-IPv6-address>} command configures a static OSPFv3 neighbor on the interface for point-to-multipoint networks. Static neighbors are required on non-broadcast networks where automatic neighbor discovery using multicast hello packets is not possible. The neighbor IPv6 address must be the link-local IPv6 address of the neighboring router on the same link. This command is valid only on interfaces configured with the point-to-multipoint network type. It is required for non-broadcast point-to-multipoint networks. The no version of this command removes the static neighbor configuration from the interface. neighbor <neighbor-IPv6- Static neighbor IPv6 link-local address. address>. Syntax:
- no IPv6 ospfv3 {neighbor <neighbor-IPv6-address>}
- IPv6 ospfv3 neighbor 2363.

The syntax of the IPv6 ospfv3 {neighbor <neighbor-IPv6-address>} command is:
- no IPv6 ospfv3 {neighbor <neighbor-IPv6-address>}
- IPv6 ospfv3 neighbor 2363.
